headline: The Market Is Betting Trump Won’t Fix High Card Rates
summary: Donald Trump  was elected at least in part because of voter unhappiness with living costs, and their hope he might do something about it.  Among those high prices have been what it costs to borrow on a credit card.  Trump during the campaign even floated the idea of a temporary 10% cap on credit-card interest rates, less than half of what the typical rate is today.
